@database psresize.guide

@width 72

@node main "psresize.guide"

PSUtils Release 1 Patchlevel 16

NAME

psresize - multiple pages per sheet


SYNOPSIS
@{b}psresize@{ub} [@{b}-w@{ub}@{i}width@{ui}] [@{b}-h@{ub}@{i}height@{ui}] [@{b}-p@{ub}@{i}paper@{ui}] [@{b}-W@{ub}@{i}width@{ui}] [@{b}-H@{ub}@{i}height@{ui}] [@{b}-P@{ub}@{i}paper@{ui}]
         [@{b}-q@{ub}] [@{i}infile@{ui} [@{i}outfile@{ui}] ]


@{i}`Online help' : @{ui} @{b}psresize -?@{ub}

DESCRIPTION

@{i}Psresize@{ui} rescales and centres a document on a different size
of paper. The input PostScript file should follow the Adobe Document
Structuring Conventions.

The @{b}-w@{ub} option gives the output paper width, and the @{b}-h@{ub}
option gives the output paper height, normally specified in @{b}"cm"@{ub}
or @{b}"in"@{ub} to convertPostScript's points (1/72 of an inch) to
centimeters or inches.

The @{b}-p@{ub} option can be used as an alternative, to set the output paper
size to @{b}a3, a4, a5, b5, letter, legal, tabloid, statement, executive,
folio, quarto@{ub} or @{b}10x14@{ub}.

The default output paper size is @{b}a4@{ub}.

The @{b}-W@{ub} option gives the input paper width, and the @{b}-H@{ub}
option gives the input paper height.

The @{b}-P@{ub} option can be used as an alternative, to set the input
paper size.

The default input paper size is @{b}a4@{ub}.

@{i}Psresize@{ui} normally prints the page numbers of the pages output; the
@{b}-q@{ub} option suppresses this.


EXAMPLES

The following command can be used to convert a document on A4 size paper to
letter size paper:

psresize -PA4 -pletter in.ps out.ps


